the selling or buying of goods and technology or of financial and
                                 technical services, including where they are located in third
                                 countries for their transfer to another third country;

a claim for the recognition or enforcement, including by the
                                 procedure of exequatur, of a judgment, an arbitration award or an
                                 equivalent decision, wherever made or given;

‘territory of the Union’ means the territories of the Member States to
                          which the Treaty is applicable, under the conditions laid down in the
                          Treaty, including their airspace;

necessary for official purposes of consular missions or international
                           organisations enjoying immunities in accordance with international law
                           located in the specified territories;

any natural or legal person, entity or body which has been found by an
                           arbitral, judicial or administrative decision to have infringed the
                           prohibitions set out in this Regulation;

to any legal person, entity or body, inside or outside the territory of
                           the Union, which is incorporated or constituted under the law of a Member
                           State;
